const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Can the AI assess chimney damage from photos?",
    answer: "Chimney damage assessment requires physical access — tapping mortar joints, checking pot stability, probing crack depth, and evaluating flue integrity. The AI cannot provide visual diagnosis from photographs. It does respond constructively to every image — acknowledging the visible deterioration, asking about the chimney age, whether the flue is currently serving an appliance, the building height and access, and whether any material has fallen. Every photograph attaches to your lead for inspection at height."
  },
  {
    question: "What about multi-message chimney threads?",
    answer: "Chimney conversations evolve across multiple messages — a homeowner sends a photo of the brown stain, then explains it appeared two years ago, then mentions the fireplace was sealed, then asks about costs. The AI maintains the entire history and assembles one comprehensive chimney lead with fault type, duration, history, chimney position, and homeowner contact details."
  },
