    question: "How much does AI WhatsApp cost for chimney specialists?",
    answer: `WhatsApp is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as a channel add-on. A chimney rebuild generates £1,500 to £5,000. A full flue relining with insulation generates £800 to £2,500. Securing one stove installer's regular lining programme — where a swift WhatsApp confirmation cements a recurring monthly relationship — provides ongoing revenue that eclipses the annual channel cost.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I take over a WhatsApp conversation?",
    answer: "Post one reply in any active thread and control transfers to you permanently. Most chimney specialists allow the AI to extract the initial details — fault type, chimney position, building age, flue status, and urgency — then engage directly to discuss the inspection schedule, structural requirements, or liner specification."
  },
  {
    question: "How is WhatsApp data from chimney enquiries protected?",
    answer: "Every WhatsApp message — chimney damage photographs, property addresses, structural details, flue condition descriptions, HETAS references, and sender contact information — is encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Your data stays exclusively with you. No project details reach competing chimney firms or are repurposed for any secondary use."
